retrospect, do you think that Pergator got a bum 
rap from the Depression? To a considerable

20:44.277 --> 20:47.741
extent, yes. Do you think that Roosevelt took 
credit for things that he really possibly wasn't

20:47.761 --> 20:54.731
responsible for? That's true. Now, I'm not saying 
he didn't do a lot of good things. He did, here and

21:01.204 --> 21:02.726
here. And some of the things that Hoover was not 
able to legislate

21:03.427 --> 21:13.640
for the simple fact that he didn't have a majority 
in Congress. Why, Roosevelt got in there, and

21:14.882 --> 21:24.694
bingo, why, banks closing and everything 
happening there, why, he could get most anything

21:14.882 --> 21:24.694
through Congress. Do you remember the elections 
of 32

21:25.484 --> 21:32.680
and 36? I do. After you left the CCC town, what did 
you proceed to do? I went to work with the George G.

21:38.153 --> 21:42.142
Fix Company in Dallas. In Dallas? No, the name of 
the company. What type of company was that?

21:52.938 --> 21:53.519
Correction. Is there? Correction. That's my 
second job. The first job I got was one of adjusting

21:58.388 --> 22:06.502
automobile insurance claims for General Motors. 
Where? in the southwest region, Texas. I was in

22:13.111 --> 22:18.070
Houston, Nacogdoches, Corpus Christi, And I 
worked through this territory. How long did you go

22:21.646 --> 22:23.568
back? About a year and a half. And then you went to 
the fixed company? And then I went to the fixed

22:26.951 --> 22:28.793
company. I want to get back to engineering. Okay. 
That's what I was trying to do. Okay. It is an

22:33.097 --> 22:34.419
engineering company. Is it still in existence? 
